<item>
            <title>[SPR-2505] Allow XML config shortcuts for plurality</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2505</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since 80% of the time assignments are simple, it should be possible to reduce XML clutter still further by just allowing these in one line.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;example:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;property name=&quot;myProperty1&quot; ref=&quot;myBean1&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;property name=&quot;myProperty2&quot; ref=&quot;myBean2&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;property name=&quot;myProperty3&quot; ref=&quot;myBean3&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can be written as:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;property refs=&quot;myProperty1=myBean1,myProperty2=myBean2,myProperty3=myBean3&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Similarly, setting values on properties can also be shortened:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;property name=&quot;myProperty&quot; value=&quot;hello&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;property name=&quot;myProperty&quot; value=&quot;hello&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;property name=&quot;myProperty&quot; value=&quot;hello&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can be written as:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;property  vals=&quot;myProperty1=val1,myProperty2=val2,myProperty3=val3&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Of course, there is most likely a better syntax for these plural assignments.&lt;/p&gt;




</description>
